		<div>Yes, expand Mistmoore and perhaps Unrest, those are 2 of my favorite zones in the game, and very small (castle somewhat large and house, but expand the outdoor portion).<br />
<br />
In general (though maybe a programming nightmare), perhaps something could be done ala LDoN zone instancing, except attach the instanced zones to various old world zones (similar to the Feerott-Fear connection). However, these pocket zones would be instanced not for 90 minutes, but for days or weeks. If each of these zones contained some uber-boss-mob01, the zones could be re-instanced (or vanish for a coupla days?) when uber-boss-mob01 has been terminated. Certainly a concept that can be toyed with .....<br />
<br />
I was farming in EK once when all of a sudden HGs started popping all over the place, it was quite amazing. There was no event announcement, and I got my ranger buddy there and he saw about 60 HGs on track lol. I saw them pop one by one, 4 or 5 in a line and then they would all walk off to the hill, then another 4 or 5. It was bizarre. I still don't know what it was all about, someone said maybe a GM was playing around, shrug.<br />
<br />
If something like that could be easily implemented, it would be awesome. However, either the high levels would get bored or the low levels would get creamed no doubt. Seems like there always used to be more GM events as well, those were always fun and would draw people to the specific zone.</div>
