	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>LDoN: Change the faction hits to matter. DGuk should raise faction with live frogloks. Mistmoore should raise faction with either the same factions that regular Mistmoore does (although those were always sort of lame) or Faydwer guards. Carry that over to all the dungeons.<br />
<br />
Guk: When the new engine goes in, make all the frogs match.<br />
<br />
Gukta/Innothule: Put in more ways to raise faction in Gukta. It's stupidly hard now.<br />
<br />
Swamp of No Hope: The frogloks here should have a faction that can be raised, and their town should have banks and merchants and all the rest. Right now, it serves no purpose except for iksar newbies to raid, and they don't do that, so it's just ... there. It's cool looking, but it serves no purpose -- even the epic fights take place outside the city.<br />
<br />
Steamfont Mountains: Consider redoing Miragul's cave as an LDoN dungeon with minotaurs, rogue clockworks and undead.<br />
<br />
Ak'Anon/Kaladim: Reactivate the arenas in each of these. Consider putting in a new cave zone that connects the two of them, but is about equal to Dagnor's in danger level -- the Underfoot of Faydwer.<br />
<br />
Dalnir: Revamp. Oh, lordy, revamp this zone. Neat dungeon, but such a mess.<br />
<br />
Jaggedpine Forest: We need the Unkempt Woods, with their evil druids (and make their goddess a selectable choice for evil druid PLAYER characters). Continue the Qeynos badge storyline beyond fighting gnolls in JP.<br />
<br />
Faydwer: We need a free zone added here, the only original continent, to my recollection, never to get one. There's several good choices, pick one.<br />
<br />
Crushbone: Consider tweaking CB to have a seperate area that can serve as a base for evils in Faydwer, which they do not have.<br />
<br />
Antonica: Give us an alternate route to Gunthak. It's silly that we have to sail there from Odus, just because Stonebrunt Mountains were under-used. Make it dangerous travel through high level KOS troll territory, but give us an overland route from Innothule.<br />
<br />
Runnyeye: Give us Chardok-style quests to ally with the Pickclaw Goblins. Runnyeye is halfway there to being an evils town. Let's make siding with them against the halfies and evil eyes have a benefit.<br />
<br />
Permafrost: We were promised a revamp of this almost two years ago. Let's see it already.<br />
<br />
Odus: We could use a visible conflict between the Heretics and Erudites. A scripted event would be nice, but just making their NPCs KOS to one another would be a start. Just setting up the pathing so that they periodically head towards each others' city and duke it out would add a lot to this zone.<br />
<br />
Kerra Ridge: Make this a full-fledged cat city, complete with faction bonuses for Vah Shir, or torch it and make it into some sort of fallen feral XP zone. But do SOMETHING with this. And if you keep it the way it is, find a way to make faction matter there -- you can slaughter far too many without consequence and turning in rat teeth would take weeks of real life time to raise even a single step. Silly in both regards.<br />
<br />
Stonebrunt Mountains: There should be a way to get there other than running through a newbie dungeon. That's disruptive and makes the dungeon less used, not more used. Put a soulbinder in with the kitties. A single worthwhile quest series linking Kejek, Kerra and the Vah Shir would be kickass.<br />
<br />
Gunthak: Make faction matter. Players should be able to take sides with the pirates and lots of troll players would love to be able to replace Grobb with Broken Skull Rock if you did this.<br />
<br />
Kunark: It should be easier for evils to raise their faction. While I agree with having the different experience for goods and evils there, it's just TOO punative for evils.<br />
<br />
Tower of Frozen Shadows: Make the mirrors work. It's just stupid that even the lore for the zone (available via Identify spell) says the final key does something that's never been true. It won't break anything to make those mirrors give access to each level individually, and make the last one go directly to either Odus or the Plane of Shadow. (My preference would be the latter.)<br />
<br />
Velious: With the change to ST 2.0, there should be more venues for getting Sleeper's Keys that don't involve killing dragons -- the dragons WANT you in Sleeper's. Killing them shouldn't be the easiest way in. Consider making the turn-in a group flag or group keying -- my guild is about the only one that's spent any real time in ST on Vazaelle in the past year. When the wizard has primal, you know something's gone awry.<br />
<br />
Luclin: Serious help is needed here, most of it lore-related. Let's see the two sides of the Combine hate each other. Again, just make them KOS to start off with. Nerf PC XP down to a more reasonable level and raise the XP level in other zones at the same time. Give us more Velious-style quests that put the forces against one another, and force players to make a choice between sides. (And yes, the one major quest that exists right now initially depends on being non-KOS to both sides -- players will figure out how to deal with this on their own.) Make the lore about the cats and the grimlings available to those not willing to suffer through a lot of timesinks. And most importantly of all, PLANE OF SHADOW as a free zone, ASAP, and let us fight Luclin. She should be a post-VT threat, of course.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
