		<!-- message -->
		<div>Instancing.  Overall alot of the old zones would be enhanced greatly if they took the good parts of LDoN, which basically means cutting Morden et al out of the picture, and added instanced zones to several older zones.  Like they did with Sol C.<br />
<br />
Ideas of instanced content:<br />
<br />
- Minotaurs in the Steamfont Mountains.<br />
- Ghosts etc. in Unrest<br />
- Crushbone orcs in Crushbone<br />
- Undead in Kithicor<br />
- Evil eyes in Beholder<br />
- Goblins in Permafrost, Runnyeye and Sol A<br />
- Grimlings in Grimling Caves<br />
- Vampyres in Tenebrous Mountains or Katta<br />
- Wyverns in the Skyfire Mountains<br />
- Werewolves in West and North Karana (with the quest being handed out by those werewolf hunters!)<br />
<br />
I am sure there could be many more.  My idea is to create content suitable for all levels (via instancing) in old world zones that utilizes old world lore.  In every case, the NPC you get the instancing from would be someone who needs help or someone who has a quest that needs doing. <br />
<br />
Revamping.  The main zones that need revamping imho are ones where you could bring about a logical explanation for the revamp.  Cazic Thule made sense because of its proximity to Fear and because the place is a temple to, well, Cazic Thule.  City of Mist did not make sense because the mobs just changed for no apparent reason.  Runnyeye made sense because it was a rival clan of goblins taking charge.  Grobb didn't make sense because trolls &gt; frogs.  <br />
<br />
That being said I think the place that most begs for revamping is Luclin.  Katta and Seru are way too close to each other and have way too much hatred for one another to not have some areas switching hands on a regular basis.<br />
<br />
edit:  lol after reading Whizbang's post directly above mine I am ready to pay him out of my meager earnings to take over the story implementation in the game.  But I know I couldn't afford him.  <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" /></div>
