	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>I like Whizbang's ideas a great deal. But in addition to those, one thing they might consider adding to old zones is triggerable raid content for small groups of time-limited but higher level players. I'm thinking something along the lines of Xanamech or the dragon in Veksar for folks in the high 50s and up, and perhaps stuff for people in the Vox/Naggy range and lower as well.<br />
<br />
Frankly, while there is a lot of talk about LDoN being for the casual player, I found it boring and it was useless to me as a time-limited player as far as any gear upgrades go. Only the top point stuff is an upgrade over the gear I have from raiding, and I simply don't have the play time to do that much LDoN this year even if I didn't get bored silly doing it. I'd much rather take my 2-4 hrs play time a week and spend them raiding, but sadly, now that we've beaten all of Velious and most of Luclin other than Emp and VT, there isn't much progression raiding that we can do when getting 30 people on is considered fabulous turnout, and most folks only make 1-2 raids a month.<br />
<br />
I accept that my play style means I'm not seeing Time anytime soon, and that is my choice -- but having some non-progression raiding other than BoT towers that didn't involve flagging or racing would be a boon to guilds like mine and players like me. If they are working on old zones, one way to revitalize them would be PoI and Veksar style quests to spawn triggerable boss mobs. LoY actually has a few good ones of these also.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
