	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>As Whizbang said already, I would love to see the Katta and Seru cities get revamped. At the moment, there are so many NPC's in those zones that do absolutely nothing. It would be nice to see them offering quests etc to aid their cause against each other.<br />
At the moment, they seem to have a 'live and let live' attitude to each other.<br />
<br />
It would be interesting if you could gain faction with Seru and recieve a quest from him to kill the freshly cured Tsaph Katta in the same way that Tormax wants Yelinak dead. The battle could take place in an instance if there is nowhere appropriate in the current zones available.<br />
<br />
Also, old loots should be upgraded to be in line with new items coming out that are the same difficulty to obtain. These days, Flowing Black Robes and various Fear / Hate Planar armour etc is inferior to rewards to the new newbie quests that are given from level 1-15. Even Velious gear looks decidedly rusty these days, but still is much harder to obtain than something from a newer, shinier expansion.<br />
<br />
It would also be nice if players could obtain Focus gear that is appropriate to thier level without having to go to the bazaar and purchase it... Looking at the Focus 1 and 2 items, they are impossible to get solo or even grouped for the most part until you have already surpassed the level where they would be useful. Level 3 and 4 focii are hard to get too, but since they are near the upper levels of the game, levelling does not remedy the situation whilst making the reward obsolete.<br />
<br />
In all, I wish that Luclin would get a major makeover. There is so much lore there, if you dig, but none of it is used. It feels like they got halfway through writing the story and the boss came out and said 'We're launching next week, finish any quest you're on and make sure the zone doesn't crash.'.<br />
<br />
Back in the Old World, it would be nice to see zones that aren't totally outclassed by newer zones in terms of exp mod. Nobody does Old World or Kunark dungeons any more. Well, noone seems to do dungeons at all since LDoN, but that is a different rant. :P I still miss stomping around Lguk, killing the undead froggies. Pity the only reason to go there these days is to farm faction or dubious quality loot which most level 15's would turn down if offered to them.<br />
<br />
A possible solution, though likely unpopular in this age of twinking, would be to revamp older dungeons, make them good places to exp instead of the LDoN yawnfest, but up the amount of NODROP loot / quest items to discourage farming (say leave the original drop table as it was but add another NODROP table to the list). Quest items would be optimal for this of course, but it requires more work...</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt2">
		
