<br />
I said this on EQLive today, but... SolusekA/B is practially crying out for a LDoN theme of its own - goblins, kobolds, bats, bugs, undead/steampunk gnome Klik'Anon remnants, rogue Solusek Mining Co. clockworks lead by Dark Reflection saboteurs, efreeti, fire/lava elementals, imps, fire drakes, deranged Temple of Sol Ro fanatics (<img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" />) and so on.<br />
<br />
West Karana: The other 3 Karanas aren't too bad (although I have some ideas after this for them) but West Karana has to <b>still</b> be the most pointless zone ever created for EQ. Some ideas to fix it on the sly without needing new zone geometry or anything like that:<br />
- Add a translocator gnome at the wizard spires who'll port you to the crossroads near the Qeynos Hills zone.<br />
- Turn the undead battlefield into a scripted ring event.<br />
- At least 3 or 4 more bandit camps. Add named bandit leaders to all the camps (a couple of levels higher) with approprite loot.<br />
- Add a DAoC-style fixed horse route from first tower to the spires, via the roads for most of it.<br />
- More quests from the Millers and other farmers.<br />
- A camp of Bloodsabers, plotting to reintroduce the plague.<br />
- A camp of exiled Splitpaws, who fled the takeover of PAw but are now trying to build a new home (after having rested and recuperated in Blackburrow)<br />
- Fix the ogre (possible) quest.<br />
- Add some pike (barracuda model) to the river...with a rare named one (aka the one that got away)<br />
- Add quests &amp; scripting to the barbarian fishing/lion-hunting/clover-gathering village<br />
- Add a script of a (low-level) named HG hassling one of the human hamlets for 'protection money'. Add a quest to kill the giant and turn in the head for a reward.<br />
- A whole bunch of new quests tied to all of this stuff. <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" /><br />
<br />
And so on.<br />
<br />
Idea for the rest of the Karanas:<br />
NK: <br />
- A bandit camp in the west side of the zone that respawns as a werewolf camp at night.<br />
<br />
EK:<br />
- Um...Do <b>something</b> with the named gnoll reaver. Loot, new quest, something.<br />
- A quest or two in the barb village<br />
- A quest or two in the human hamlets.<br />
- A quest or two at the druid circle<br />
- Add more stuff at the bottom of the canyon (static spawn spiders with a 'webbing' attack (snare/root proc) and similar would be a start).<br />
<br />
SK:<br />
- An exiled Splitpaw camp.<br />
- Set up a mini-Velious between Splitpaw exiles, Paw gnolls, Aviaks and Centaur with a handful of quests for each (and appropriate faction hits when killing stuff)<br />
- Fix Cracktusk's quest!<br />
<br />
<br />
I've also got a whole write-up for a more involved Befallen revamp involving Marnek and the Burning Dead tucked away somewhere, but I'll have to search for it. <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" /></div>
